<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="quoteright" style="width:300px;"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:129.67%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/marais_3086.jpg" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/marais_3086.jpg" width="300" height="389"></div></div><div class="acaptionright" style="width:300px;">No, that's not the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/BlueManGroup" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/BlueManGroup">Blue Man Group</a>.</div><p></p><div class="indent"><em>"Humanity. What a wonderful puppet show! How could I get bored of it?"</em><div class="indent">&mdash; <strong>Fant&ocirc;mas</strong></div></div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p><em>Fant&ocirc;mas</em> is a 1964 French film <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationDecay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationDecay">very loosely based</a> on the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Fantomas" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Fantomas">novels of the same name</a>. It turned the title character (a criminal and anarchist in the books) into a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JamesBond" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JamesBond">Blofeld</a>-esque <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DiabolicalMastermind" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DiabolicalMastermind">supervillain</a> and spawned two sequels, <em>Fant&ocirc;mas Unleashed</em> in 1965 and <em>Fant&ocirc;mas Against Scotland Yard</em> in 1967.</p><p>The first film sees Fant&ocirc;mas (played by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JeanMarais" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JeanMarais">Jean Marais</a> and voiced by Raymond Pellegrin) being very angry at Fandor (also played by Jean Marais), a journalist who has written a fictional (and ridiculous) interview of him. After bombing Fandor's editorial offices, he kidnaps Fandor, threatens to kill him, iron-brands him, and goes about ruining the journalist's reputation by committing a sensational theft wearing a Fandor mask. He also kidnaps Fandor's fianc&eacute;e H&eacute;l&egrave;ne (Myl&egrave;ne Demongeot). Hot on the trail is buffoonish police commissioner Juve (<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LouisDeFunes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LouisDeFunes">Louis de Fun&egrave;s</a>). Fant&ocirc;mas then starts committing robberies with a mask imitating Juve's face to get rid of him.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><p>In the second film, <em>Fant&ocirc;mas Unleashed</em> (<em>Fant&ocirc;mas se d&eacute;cha&icirc;ne</em>), Fant&ocirc;mas <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KidnappedScientist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KidnappedScientist">kidnaps several scientists</a> to conceive devices for his nefarious plans, and Juve and Fandor go after him in <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/Italy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/Italy">Italy</a>.</p><p>In the third film, <em>Fant&ocirc;mas Against Scotland Yard</em> (<em>Fant&ocirc;mas contre Scotland Yard</em>), Fant&ocirc;mas ransoms several billionaires, threatening to kill them if they don't oblige to his "tax on the right to live". Juve and Fandor step up to protect one of these billionaires, the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/Scotland" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/Scotland">Scottish</a> Lord Mac Rashley, and use him as bait to try catching Fant&ocirc;mas.</p><p></p><hr><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><h2>The <em>Fant&ocirc;mas</em> movies provides examples of:</h2><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="toggleAllFolders();">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;open/close all folders&nbsp; </div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder0');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Series-wide&nbsp;</div><div id="folder0" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AntagonistTitle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AntagonistTitle">Antagonist Title</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BaldOfEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BaldOfEvil">Bald of Evil</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas, with his mask on.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BumblingSidekick" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BumblingSidekick">Bumbling Sidekick</a>:<ul><li> Commissioner Juve for Fandor, most of the time.</li><li> Inspector Bertrand, for Commissioner Juve.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatchPhrase" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatchPhrase">Catchphrase</a>: Every time Fant&ocirc;mas manages to escape:<div class="indent"><strong>Juve:</strong> I'll catch you , Fant&ocirc;mas, I'LL CATCH YOU!!</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChessmaster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChessmaster">The Chessmaster</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaChief" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaChief">Da Chief</a>: Commissioner Juve is a gruff and authoritarian boss who is constantly shouting orders at his subordinates. For bonus points, he sometimes smoke a cigar and wears suspenders.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreepyMonotone" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreepyMonotone">Creepy Monotone</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Determinator" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Determinator">Determinator</a>: Commissioner Juve. It doesn't matter how many obstacles Fant&ocirc;mas throws at him; he stays in hot pursuit whatever the cost, sometimes at great risk to himself, and comes <em>very close</em> to catching the evil mastermind several times.<div class="indent"><strong>Juve:</strong> I'll catch you, Fant&ocirc;mas, I'll catch you!</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DiabolicalMastermind" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DiabolicalMastermind">Diabolical Mastermind</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaEditor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaEditor">Da Editor</a>: Fandor's boss, played by Robert Dalban.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilGenius" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilGenius">Evil Genius</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilLaugh" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilLaugh">Evil Laugh</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas does at least one per film, at the end usually. Not really hammy but still sinister.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilPlan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilPlan">Evil Plan</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas is always planning something evil.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilSoundsDeep" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilSoundsDeep">Evil Sounds Deep</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas was voiced by Raymond Pellegrin, whose voice was notably deeper than Jean Marais'.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExpressiveMask" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExpressiveMask">Expressive Mask</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas' masked face can be expressive (at least as expressive a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Practicaleffects" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Practicaleffects">practical</a> rubber mask can possibly get).</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheFaceless" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheFaceless">The Faceless</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas is always seen wearing an intimidating bluish latex mask.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FauxAffablyEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FauxAffablyEvil">Faux Affably Evil</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas is always very polite even when he explains you that he plans to remove your brain from your body to create a new kind of slave.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foil">Foil</a>: Juve to Fant&ocirc;mas. Both are leader of large group of men (Juve is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaChief" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaChief">Da Chief</a> and Fant&ocirc;mas is the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DiabolicalMastermind" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DiabolicalMastermind">Diabolical Mastermind</a>) and both are skilled with gadgets and disguises (Juve to a lesser extent but still visible in <em>Fant&ocirc;mas Unleashed</em>).</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GentlemanThief" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GentlemanThief">Gentleman Thief</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas is a supercriminal, and he's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WickedCultured" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WickedCultured">Wicked Cultured</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheHero">The Hero</a>: Fandor fits the bill, although he starts off as a liar when <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoingForTheBigScoop" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoingForTheBigScoop">Going for the Big Scoop</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntrepidReporter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntrepidReporter">Intrepid Reporter</a>: Fandor is a reporter, and he's perfectly capable of punching his way through Fant&ocirc;mas' mooks.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini">Karma Houdini</a>: No matter what the heroes try, Fant&ocirc;mas will always manage to escape.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LatexPerfection" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LatexPerfection">Latex Perfection</a>:<ul><li> Fant&ocirc;mas' masks when he wants to impersonate someone. This also includes gloves reproducing fingerprints. In the first film, both Jean Marais's and Louis de Fun&eacute;s's facial features are slightly exaggerated (larger eyebrows or ears) when Fant&ocirc;mas impersonates them. Played straight in later movies.</li><li> In <em>Fant&ocirc;mas Unleashed</em>, Fandor also uses a perfect disguise.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Leitmotif" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Leitmotif">Leitmotif</a>: Both Fant&ocirc;mas and Juve have their own. Fant&ocirc;mas uses the <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jKLs28MWQzc">ominous main theme<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> of the movies. Juve has a <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Cntz5XQYbI">much more comedic one.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> Used to great effect during chase scenes by alternating the two.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LighterAndSofter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LighterAndSofter">Lighter and Softer</a>: When compared to the books and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SilentFilms" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SilentFilms">Silent Films</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MalevolentMaskedMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MalevolentMaskedMan">Malevolent Masked Man</a>: Just look at the page's picture.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasterOfDisguise" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasterOfDisguise">Master of Disguise</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas' disguises can fool anyone.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MsFanservice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MsFanservice">Ms. Fanservice</a>: H&eacute;l&egrave;ne, Fandor's fianc&eacute;e, played by Myl&egrave;ne Demongeot.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PhantomThief" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PhantomThief">Phantom Thief</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaningfulName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaningfulName">naturally</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SayMyName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SayMyName">Say My Name</a>: Many a character will dramatically exclaim "Fant&ocirc;mas!" when confronted with the villain. Commissioner Juve's yells have reached memetic status.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SettingUpdate" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SettingUpdate">Setting Update</a>: The story of the books and silent films takes place in the Belle Epoque (pre-<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/WorldWarI" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/WorldWarI">World War I</a> France). This version adjusts to its decade, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSixties" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSixties">The '60s</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SoftGlass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SoftGlass">Soft Glass</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas or Fandor have no trouble jumping through windows.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpotlightStealingSquad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpotlightStealingSquad">Spotlight-Stealing Squad</a>: The series is fondly remembered partly because <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LouisDeFunes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LouisDeFunes">Louis de Fun&egrave;s</a> starred in. And his role got increasingly important screentime as the series went on.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SympatheticInspectorAntagonist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SympatheticInspectorAntagonist">Sympathetic Inspector Antagonist</a>: Commissioner Juve. More like "sympathetic inspector protagonist", actually.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainExitStageLeft" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainExitStageLeft">Villain: Exit, Stage Left</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas always manages to escape.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WickedCultured" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WickedCultured">Wicked Cultured</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas</li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder1');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>Fant&ocirc;mas</em>&nbsp;</div><div id="folder1" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton">Berserk Button</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas hates to be ridiculed in the public eye. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoNotTauntCthulhu" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoNotTauntCthulhu">Fandor will learn it the hard way</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallingCard" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallingCard">Calling Card</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas regularly leaves one behind. The first theft in the first movie has him buying priceless jewelry with a check under a fake name. The writings on the check erase themselves soon after he leaves the jeweler and all is left is Fant&ocirc;mas' actual signature.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CarSkiing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CarSkiing">Car Skiing</a>: It happens when Fandor tries to control the car sabotaged by Lady Beltham.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChaseScene" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChaseScene">Chase Scene</a>: In the last part of the film, Fant&ocirc;mas is chased by Juve, Fandor and the police.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClearMyName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClearMyName">Clear My Name</a>:<ul><li> Inverted: Fant&ocirc;mas wants to be <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDreaded" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDreaded">feared</a>, not to be mocked/considered as a myth by the medias, so he commits thefts, drive-by shootings and bombing attacks.</li><li> Played straight by Fandor and Juve after Fant&ocirc;mas has impersonated them.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrazyPrepared" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrazyPrepared">Crazy-Prepared</a>:<div class="indent"><strong>Fant&ocirc;mas:</strong> I'm a very organized man.</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CruelAndUnusualDeath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CruelAndUnusualDeath">Cruel and Unusual Death</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas plans to use Fandor's brain (and later Juve's) to create a new kind of slave.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkMistress" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkMistress">Dark Mistress</a>: Lady Beltham.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EngineeredPublicConfession" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EngineeredPublicConfession">Engineered Public Confession</a>: When Fant&ocirc;mas explains that he will charm H&eacute;l&egrave;ne, Fandor discreetly makes a phone call to Lady Beltham, who can hear everything about Fant&ocirc;mas's plan to cheat on her. Consequently, Lady Beltham decides to release Fandor and H&eacute;l&egrave;ne.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FacialCompositeFailure" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FacialCompositeFailure">Facial Composite Failure</a>: After the casino attack, the police uses a light box over which a cop places transparencies with various pre-drawn facial features and the criminal ends being recognised as Juve. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InvertedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InvertedTrope">Inverted</a>, because the facial composite is quite efficient, even if leads to arresting the wrong person because the actual criminal, Fant&ocirc;mas, used <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LatexPerfection" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LatexPerfection">Latex Perfection</a> to impersonate Juve.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FoodInterrogation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FoodInterrogation">Food Interrogation</a>: This is Commissioner Juve's method for making perps sweat. He eats before one while denying him food. Fandor stays rather unfazed. Later, after Fant&ocirc;mas commits a crime while wearing Juve's face, the tables are turned. It is now Juve being interrogated, while his usual sidekick Bertrand is doing the eating.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HighHeelFaceTurn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HighHeelFaceTurn">High-Heel&#150;Face Turn</a>: Subverted. After Fant&ocirc;mas' consort learns that he's planning to replace her with Helene, she breaks her and Fandor out of captivity and provides them with a get-away car. Without brakes.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LeaningOnTheFourthWall" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LeaningOnTheFourthWall">Leaning on the Fourth Wall</a>: At the end of the first film, when <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheEnd" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheEnd">The End</a> appears, Juve says: "This is not the end! We will meet again!"</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagicBrakes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagicBrakes">Magic Brakes</a>: Happens in the car given to Fandor and H&eacute;l&egrave;ne by Lady Beltham. Partly <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustifiedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustifiedTrope">Justified</a>, because Fandor says that the brakes and the gear box are sabotaged and because the car is in a mountain road.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OminousPipeOrgan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OminousPipeOrgan">Ominous Pipe Organ</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas has a fully automatic organ in his lair in the first movie. As Fandor <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WakingUpElsewhere" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WakingUpElsewhere">wakes up from his kidnapping</a> in the lair, it starts to play an ominous piece to announce Fant&ocirc;mas' arrival. <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gcuw99UGFzA">Fant&ocirc;mas also plays it manually<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> at one point.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OrWasItADream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OrWasItADream">Or Was It a Dream?</a>: At first, when Fandor wakes up in his flat, he thinks his vision of Fant&ocirc;mas was a dream. Then H&eacute;l&egrave;ne notices that he has a bump on his head, and he notices the "F" that Fant&ocirc;mas tattooed on his chest, so he realizes that it was not a dream.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PetTheDog" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PetTheDog">Pet the Dog</a>: When Fant&ocirc;mas interacts with H&eacute;l&egrave;ne, he behaves like a gentleman.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PunchPunchPunchUhOh" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PunchPunchPunchUhOh">Punch! Punch! Punch! Uh Oh...</a>: As Fandor wakes up in Fant&ocirc;mas' lair, he gives a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoodOldFisticuffs" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoodOldFisticuffs">good beating</a> to some mooks. When he punches Fant&ocirc;mas in the face and the torso, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoSell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoSell">nothing happens</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheScapegoat" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheScapegoat">The Scapegoat</a>: Fandor and Juve in the first movie.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScareChord" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScareChord">Scare Chord</a>: Plays when Fandor is kidnapped in the first movie.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlaveBrand" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlaveBrand">Slave Brand</a>: On their first encounter, Fant&ocirc;mas brands Fandor with an "F" on the chest to remind him that "From now on, you belong to me."</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SupervillainLair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SupervillainLair">Supervillain Lair</a>: A French castle.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrainEscape" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrainEscape">Train Escape</a>: During the final <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChaseScene" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChaseScene">Chase Scene</a>, Fant&ocirc;mas jumps on a moving train, followed by Fandor and Juve. Fant&ocirc;mas then unhooks the wagons to escape from them.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VehicularSabotage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VehicularSabotage">Vehicular Sabotage</a>: Lady Beltham sabotages the brakes and the gear box of the car that she gives to Fandor and H&eacute;l&egrave;ne to escape.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainousCrush" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainousCrush">Villainous Crush</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas has one on H&eacute;l&egrave;ne.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhosOnFirst" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhosOnFirst">Who's on First?</a>: The interrogation scene between inspector Juve and Fandor:<div class="indent"><strong>Juve:</strong> Speak up! So the article was a lie, wasn't it? <br><strong>Fandor:</strong> I told you already, it is. <br><strong>Juve:</strong> You say it's a lie, and now everyone says it's true! <br><strong>Fandor:</strong> Well, it is true. <br><strong>Juve:</strong> So what's true, that everyone says it's true? <br><strong>Fandor:</strong> No, but it's true that it's a lie. <br><strong>Juve:</strong> So it's true that it's a lie? But-I-Wait-Okay, let's say that you're not lying, then why did Fant&ocirc;mas kidnap you last night if it was a lie? <br><strong>Fandor:</strong> Well, for exactly the reason I was lying! <br><strong>Juve:</strong> He's lying. He's lying! He's LYING! HE'S LYING! <br><strong>Fandor:</strong> When exactly you claim that I lied? When I said that I lied, or when I lied that I said&mdash; <br><strong>Juve:</strong> ENOUGH! Be quiet, be quiet!</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WomanScorned" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WomanScorned">Woman Scorned</a>: After Fant&ocirc;mas abducts Fandor and his fianc&eacute;e, he <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustBetweenYouAndMe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustBetweenYouAndMe">reveals</a> to Fandor that he wanted to make her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IHaveYouNowMyPretty" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IHaveYouNowMyPretty">his concubine</a> instead of his current one. Fandor stages an <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EngineeredPublicConfession" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EngineeredPublicConfession">Engineered Public Confession</a>, and she helps them escape prompting Fandor <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging">to mention this trope</a>. She is still evil and savvy though, so <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">she disabled the brakes on the car she provided them</span>.</li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder2');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>Fant&ocirc;mas Unleashed</em>&nbsp;</div><div id="folder2" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimatedCreditsOpening" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimatedCreditsOpening">Animated Credits Opening</a>: The animated opening sums up the events of the previous movie.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AstonishinglyAppropriateInterruption" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AstonishinglyAppropriateInterruption">Astonishingly Appropriate Interruption</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaEditor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaEditor">Da Editor</a> is ranting at Fandor for his latest paper about Fant&ocirc;mas, saying he can already hear Juve screaming... just as H&eacute;l&egrave;ne starts the TV, where commissioner Juve is giving an angry interview.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BatmanGambit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BatmanGambit">Batman Gambit</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas releases H&eacute;l&egrave;ne and tells her not to tell anything about her kidnapping. Then he sends her an invitation to a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall">Masquerade Ball</a> and a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PimpedOutDress" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PimpedOutDress">Pimped-Out Dress</a>. He plans she will either tell Fandor and Juve or be followed by them, so that he can kidnap them at the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall">Masquerade Ball</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoundAndGagged" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoundAndGagged">Bound and Gagged</a>: Juve and his interviewer end up bound and gagged on live television after Fant&ocirc;mas interrupts to take over the broadcasting.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaChief" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaChief">Da Chief</a>: The police prefect chews out Juve for being humiliated on live television by Fant&ocirc;mas.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrouchingMoronHiddenBadass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrouchingMoronHiddenBadass">Crouching Moron, Hidden Badass</a>: Commissioner Juve. His role might be purely comedic most of the time, but he guns down several Mooks and gets to save all the protagonists from captivity thanks to his gadgets.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DamselInDistress" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DamselInDistress">Damsel in Distress</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ZigZaggingTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ZigZaggingTrope">Zig-zagged</a>. H&eacute;l&egrave;ne is kidnapped by Fant&ocirc;mas, but he releases her almost immediately. After the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall">Masquerade Ball</a>, he kidnaps her again, but he kidnaps at the same time the male protagonists (Juve, Fandor and Bertrand), who are then in a far greater danger than H&eacute;l&egrave;ne. The male protagonists free themselves and rescue H&eacute;l&egrave;ne.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoNotAdjustYourSet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoNotAdjustYourSet">Do Not Adjust Your Set</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas takes over the TV transmission during an interview of Commissioner Juve. When it gets back to normal, Juve and his interviewer are <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoundAndGagged" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoundAndGagged">Bound and Gagged</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvenEvilHasStandards" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvenEvilHasStandards">Even Evil Has Standards</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WouldntHurtAChild" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WouldntHurtAChild">does not harm H&eacute;l&egrave;ne's younger brother</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlyingCar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlyingCar">Flying Car</a>: A flying <a class="urllink" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Citro<!--C3-->ABn_DS">Citro&euml;n DS<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FollowThatCar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FollowThatCar">Follow That Car</a>: Juve says "Follow that car!"... to a plane pilot, since they're pursuing Fant&ocirc;mas's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlyingCar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlyingCar">Flying Car</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GadgeteerGenius" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GadgeteerGenius">Gadgeteer Genius</a>: In the second movie, Juve has devised a fake arms/hands which allows to have a concealed hand with a gun, as well as cigars which can shoot bullets when lighted <a class="urllink" href="https://www.dailymotion.com/video/x3rg18">[1]<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>. Both of this gadgets are skillfully used by Juve when facing Fant&ocirc;mas' Goons.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoAmongMadPeople" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoAmongMadPeople">Go Among Mad People</a>: Juve is arrested by the Italian police and sent to an asylum.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoGoEnslavement" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoGoEnslavement">Go-Go Enslavement</a>: H&eacute;l&egrave;ne wears an oriental <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PimpedOutDress" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PimpedOutDress">Pimped-Out Dress</a> when she is held captive by Fant&ocirc;mas. She wears it when she escapes.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroStoleMyBike" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroStoleMyBike">Hero Stole My Bike</a>: Juve and Fandor steal the car of campers to chase after Fant&ocirc;mas in the final <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChaseScene" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChaseScene">Chase Scene</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HighClassGlass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HighClassGlass">High-Class Glass</a>: Juve's first disguise, as an Italian military officer, includes a monocle. He has some trouble with it, notably letting it fall in his teacup.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HypnoRay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HypnoRay">Hypno Ray</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas abducts a number of scientists and has them construct a hypno ray gun. After the heroes thwart his plans and free the scientists, they use the gun to placate a pair of mooks he threw at them, but Fant&ocirc;mas himself escaped before they have a chance to subdue him.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HypocriticalHumor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HypocriticalHumor">Hypocritical Humor</a>: When Juve demonstrates the gun-cigars, everybody freaks out when they go off and we have this gem:<div class="indent"><strong>Juve:</strong> Gentlemen, you are lacking calm and composure! I want a "relaxed" police! You hear me? RELAXED!</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IHaveYourWife" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IHaveYourWife">I Have Your Wife</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas holds H&eacute;l&egrave;ne's brother prisoner so that she does not tell Fandor and Juve about her kidnapping and she goes to the masquerade ball.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InstantDeathBullet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InstantDeathBullet">Instant Death Bullet</a>: Juve's one-shot cigar-guns.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KidnappedScientist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KidnappedScientist">Kidnapped Scientist</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas does this in order to build a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MindControlDevice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MindControlDevice">Mind-Control Device</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnockoutGas" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnockoutGas">Knockout Gas</a>: Mooks in diving gear come out of a fountain and takes out Juve, Fandor, H&eacute;l&egrave;ne and Bertrand by sedating them with gas weapons.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LastRequest" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LastRequest">Last Request</a>: Juve asks Fant&ocirc;mas' henchmen for a cigar as a last request. He also offer them cigars. They are actually cigar-guns.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LegCannon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LegCannon">Leg Cannon</a>: Juve has a machine gun disguised as a peg leg as part of his pirate disguise during the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall">Masquerade Ball</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LosingYourHead" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LosingYourHead">Losing Your Head</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas plans to test on Juve, Fandor and Bertrand an experiment aiming at allowing their heads live without their bodies. That is, unless H&eacute;l&egrave;ne accepts to become his new lady friend.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall">Masquerade Ball</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas organizes one and catches H&eacute;l&egrave;ne, Fandor, Juve and Bertrand.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MultiArmedAndDangerous" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MultiArmedAndDangerous">Multi-Armed and Dangerous</a>: Commissioner Juve's coat.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PaperThinDisguise" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PaperThinDisguise">Paper-Thin Disguise</a>: While this is nothing new for De Fun&egrave;s, they are more believable in the second movie: he disguises as an Italian Officer, a train steward, a hotel bellhop, a priest and a pirate at the masquerade.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThePrankster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThePrankster">The Prankster</a>: Michou, H&eacute;l&egrave;ne's younger brother, doesn't miss an opportunity to prank the adults.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PreviouslyOn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PreviouslyOn">Previously On&#133;</a>: The <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimatedCreditsOpening" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimatedCreditsOpening">Animated Credits Opening</a> doubles as this, shortly retelling the first movie.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScarpiaUltimatum" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScarpiaUltimatum">Scarpia Ultimatum</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas threatens to remove the head of Fandor, Juve and Bertrand if H&eacute;l&egrave;ne does not agree to become his partner.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SeadogPegLeg" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SeadogPegLeg">Seadog Peg Leg</a>: Juve goes to the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasqueradeBall">Masquerade Ball</a> in a pirate costume, complete with eyepatch and peg leg &mdash; doubling as a machine gun.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SequelEscalation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SequelEscalation">Sequel Escalation</a>: The first film is mostly about Fant&ocirc;mas committing several important thefts and showing to the public eye that he can be a real threat (and avenging the journalistic insult in the process). He uses mostly believable means such as his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasterOfDisguise" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasterOfDisguise">Master of Disguise</a> talents, drive-by shootings, grenade and bombing attacks. The first sequel has him planning to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeOverTheWorld" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeOverTheWorld">Take Over the World</a> from his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VolcanoLair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VolcanoLair">Volcano Lair</a> using a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MindControlDevice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MindControlDevice">Mind-Control Device</a>, with a goofier-than-ever commissioner Juve trying to stop him using <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JamesBond" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JamesBond">James Bond</a>-esque gadgets. And there's a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlyingCar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlyingCar">Flying Car</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SequelGoesForeign" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SequelGoesForeign">Sequel Goes Foreign</a>: The bulk of the story takes place in Italy (the first one was set in France).</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut">Shout-Out</a>:<div class="indent"><strong>Juve:</strong> What would people think of you if Fant&ocirc;mas was caught by a vulgar <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JamesBond" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JamesBond">00-something? We are in an era of secret agents and gadgets!</a></div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpyFiction" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpyFiction">Spy Fiction</a>: <em>Fant&ocirc;mas Unleashed</em> spoofs the use of gadgets, extravagant villain plans and lairs from Sean Connery's <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JamesBond" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JamesBond">James Bond</a></em> era (and even predates those of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/YouOnlyLiveTwice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/YouOnlyLiveTwice">You Only Live Twice</a></em>).</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SupervillainLair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SupervillainLair">Supervillain Lair</a>: A <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VolcanoLair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VolcanoLair">Volcano Lair</a>, with a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadScientistLaboratory" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadScientistLaboratory">Mad Scientist Laboratory</a> and a control pannel to activate trap doors or <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OminousPipeOrgan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OminousPipeOrgan">Ominous Pipe Organ</a> music.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TotemPoleTrench" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TotemPoleTrench">Totem Pole Trench</a>: H&eacute;l&egrave;ne's young brother and another kid disguise temselves as Fant&ocirc;mas this way.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TransformingVehicle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TransformingVehicle">Transforming Vehicle</a>: As he's pursued by the good guys, Fant&ocirc;mas's Citro&euml;n DS engages on a runway and transforms into a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlyingCar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlyingCar">Flying Car</a> to escape them.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainousCrush" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainousCrush">Villainous Crush</a>: As in the first movie, Fant&ocirc;mas has one on H&eacute;l&egrave;ne.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VolcanoLair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VolcanoLair">Volcano Lair</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas has a new lair below a volcano.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WigDressAccent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WigDressAccent">Wig, Dress, Accent</a>: Juve's Italian ticket inspector disguise.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WouldntHurtAChild" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WouldntHurtAChild">Wouldn't Hurt a Child</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas does not harm H&eacute;l&egrave;ne's younger brother.</li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder3');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>Fant&ocirc;mas Against Scotland Yard</em>&nbsp;</div><div id="folder3" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBadGuyWins" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBadGuyWins">The Bad Guy Wins</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Fant&ocirc;mas kills Lord Mac Rashley, steals the diamonds and manages to escape once more</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BedsheetGhost" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BedsheetGhost">Bedsheet Ghost</a>: Commissioner Juve and Bertrand are disguised like this.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeadPersonImpersonation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeadPersonImpersonation">Dead Person Impersonation</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas impersonates Lord Rashley after murdering him.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FakeoutEscape" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FakeoutEscape">Fakeout Escape</a>: At the end, Fant&ocirc;mas escapes in a rocket that was hidden in one of the castle's towers and takes off. Juve immediately calls the French air force, a squadron is dispatched and destroys the rocket with a missile. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Except it was a bait. Fant&ocirc;mas wasn't in the rocket, he simply escaped using the castle's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SecretUndergroundPassage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SecretUndergroundPassage">secret underground passages</a> and a <em>bicycle</em> while everyone's attention was focused on the rocket.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HuntingAccident" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HuntingAccident">Hunting "Accident"</a>: Lord Rashley's secretary plans to kill his boss during a hunting party. He does not know he is dead already and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MuggingTheMonster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MuggingTheMonster">Fant&ocirc;mas impersonates him</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItWasHereISwear" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItWasHereISwear">It Was Here, I Swear!</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas adores doing this to Juve, especially in <em>Fant&ocirc;mas Against Scotland Yard</em>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ManInAKilt" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ManInAKilt">Man in a Kilt</a>: The third and last film is set in Scotland. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LouisDeFunes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LouisDeFunes">Louis de Fun&egrave;s</a> obliged.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MuggingTheMonster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MuggingTheMonster">Mugging the Monster</a>: Lord Rashley's secretary plans to kill his boss. He does not know he is dead already and Fant&ocirc;mas impersonates him. The supervillain proves a much harder target than expected, and ends up throwing him off a cliff.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurphysBed" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurphysBed">Murphy's Bed</a>: In Lord Rashley's castle, Commissioner Juve's bed is rigged to move on wheels, pursuing Inspector Bertrand throughout the bedroom before dragging both men into a secret passage and all the way down to Fant&ocirc;mas' lair, where the villain makes them <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnOfferYouCantRefuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnOfferYouCantRefuse">an offer they can't refuse</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnOfferYouCantRefuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnOfferYouCantRefuse">An Offer You Can't Refuse</a>: Fant&ocirc;mas imposes a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackmailIsSuchAnUglyWord" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackmailIsSuchAnUglyWord">head tax</a> on the richest men in the world, threatening to kill those who do not comply.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PillowPistol" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PillowPistol">Pillow Pistol</a>: Juve keeps a gun under his pillow &mdash; probably not always, only when on this mission as he is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProperlyParanoid" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProperlyParanoid">Properly Paranoid</a>. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Then the gun's suddenly missing!</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RightForTheWrongReasons" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RightForTheWrongReasons">Right for the Wrong Reasons</a>: Juve incorrectly assumes that Fant&ocirc;mas is disguised as Lord Rashley when he is in reality just <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Gaslighting" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Gaslighting">Gaslighting</a> him, but he is right when Fant&ocirc;mas <em>really</em> impersonate Rashley. Even more ironic, the "dead" Rashley was the real Fant&ocirc;mas while the "alive" Rashley is the real one.<div class="indent"><strong>Juve:</strong> <em>[in a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BedsheetGhost" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BedsheetGhost">Bedsheet Ghost</a> disguise]</em> Now I got it, I understand everything now! It's you! <br><strong>Lord Rashley:</strong> I beg your pardon? <br><strong>Juve:</strong> You are Fant&ocirc;mas! You put the mask of Lord Mac Rashley, gimme your mask! GIMME YOUR MASK!</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SequelGoesForeign" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SequelGoesForeign">Sequel Goes Foreign</a>: The French protagonists go to Scotland this time around.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpookySeance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpookySeance">Spooky S&eacute;ance</a>: During one, the guests of Lord Rashley try to communicate with Walter Brown, a victim of Fant&ocirc;mas. Juve is scared to death.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperWindowJump" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperWindowJump">Super Window Jump</a>: At the end of the movie, Fandor jumps through a stained-glass ceiling for no particular reason.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnexplainedRecovery" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnexplainedRecovery">Unexplained Recovery</a>: A <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Mook" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Mook">mook</a> killed by one of Juve's cigars in <em>Fant&ocirc;mas Unleashed</em> is then seen alive in <em>Fant&ocirc;mas Against Scotland Yard</em> (same actor in the same role) without explanation.</li></ul></div><hr>
</div>
